race.comment: SEA ME DANCE (6) continues to knock on the door and looks ready to break through after another solid placing last time at Doomben. She was no match for a smart winner but stuck on bravely. Peaking now and gets in light with the 3kg claimer engaged. Ready to finally shed the maiden tag. CONTINENT (3) improved sharply when stepping out in trip at Ipswich, closing off strongly into second, and he has plenty of scope to progress further. KIRORO PEAK (1) chased gamely into second over 1900m on the Poly last start, and the rise in trip should suit him well. WEEKEND ARTIST (2) is inconsistent but has figures that measure up, while ZEDIQUETTE (7) deserves safe keeping despite recent failures.
